Judging from the figure in 
<bibRefCitation id="336E4B25FFE2416FC8D7E86FFC9B2178" author="Glenn, G. S. Jr." box="[657,809,259,285]" pageId="20" pageNumber="471" pagination="67 - 102" refId="ref16270" refString="Glenn, G. S. Jr. (1991) A systematic revision of Enyaliopsis Karsch 1887 (Orthoptera: Tettigoniidae, Hetrodinae). Transactions of the American Entomological Society, 117, 67 - 102. http: // www. jstor. org / stable / 25078540" type="journal article" year="1991">Glenn (1991)</bibRefCitation>
, the calling song of this species may belong to song 
<typeStatus id="88448876FFE2416FCF2AE868FA2E217B" box="[1388,1436,260,286]" pageId="20" pageNumber="471">type</typeStatus>
A (trill) (in 
<figureCitation id="CFC42A51FFE2416FCB5FE84BFEEE2127" box="[281,348,295,322]" captionStart="FIGURE 5" captionStartId="8.[151,250,1254,1278]" captionTargetBox="[158,1423,198,1221]" captionTargetId="figure-23@8.[151,1436,181,1231]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURE 5. Oscillograms of song types in Hetrodini. Song consisting A of long trills (Cosmoderus femoralis CH8627), B of broken trills (including transitions to long echemes; B1 Spalacomimus talpa, B2 Enyaliopsis jennae, B3 Enyaliopsis ephippiatus) or C of regularly repeated echemes (C1 Spalacomimus spec. near verruciferus, C2 Eugaster guyoni). 1-min-sections." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6392721" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6392721/files/figure.png" pageId="20" pageNumber="471">Fig. 5</figureCitation>
; see 
<tableCitation id="1A7D036FFFE2416FCBD5E84BFE5B2124" box="[403,489,295,321]" captionStart="TABLE 2" captionStartId="7.[151,236,476,501]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="TABLE 2. Song characteristics of Hetrodini species (for song type see Fig. 5 and text)" httpUri="http://table.plazi.org/id/0380665CFFF1417CCAD1E8B0FBBD2190" pageId="20" pageNumber="471" tableUuid="0380665CFFF1417CCAD1E8B0FBBD2190">Table 2</tableCitation>
).
</paragraph>
